Go to Azure Portal → Navigate to Virtual Machines → Select your VM.

In the VM settings, click Disks.

Click + Add data disk.

Choose Create disk (for a new disk) or Select existing disk.

Configure Name, Size, Type (Standard HDD/SSD, Premium SSD).

Click Save → Azure will attach the disk.

Initialize inside VM:

Windows VM: Use Disk Management (diskmgmt.msc) to bring the disk online, initialize, and format.
